post_text: Session Two of Parenting with Love & Logic will be held on Friday, January 24th, from 6:00-7:30 PM. Helen Abernathy & Esther Marin will facilitate the class entitled Teaching Responsibility Without Losing Their Love. Parenting with Love & Logic seeks to provide the skills needed to feel more relaxed, hopeful and positive about parenting. With each new lesson, you will discover that your job can be really enjoyable, and that you can teach personal responsibility and respect without losing your kids‚Äô love. Come learn how to use a little humor and fun while raising responsible kids. Free childcare will be provided!

Today is our fundraiser! Help us raise money for our new library!

All day today, for any order (including dine-in and take out) where Beta Academy is mentioned, Gringo's will donate 20% of the bill back to the school. Please remember to either bring the attached flyer and give it to your server / cashier OR mention Beta Academy to make sure we get credit!

Any scholar who brings in a Gringo's receipt from the fundraiser on Tuesday to their teacher will get a coupon for a dress down day which can be used during that week. If your family has multiple Beta scholars, please prepare a copy of the receipt for each scholar. Also, if you have a scholar in grades 6-10, they can bring in a copy of the receipt for a dress down day as well.

We hope to see you! Thanks for your continued support!

17 syllables - that‚Äôs all the scholars had to make an impression. 4th - 6th graders participated in a cross-curricular music project creating Haiku, a Japanese poetry form that packs a lot of emotion in a small amount of space. The project spanned several weeks as some poems were set to music on xylophones using the pentatonic scale. Selections were chosen for a final competition and the winner is Michelle Verdin from Ms. Smith‚Äôs 6th grade homeroom. This is her poem:

I‚Äôm a sunflower
I show a smile and stand tall
though I am not proud

post_text: Fourth Grade scholars have been working diligently for several weeks to complete their Taco Truck Project! Scholars were required to design a logo and truck, come up with a dynamic menu, take orders from peers, create blue prints of the layout, and finally create a three-dimensional replica of their truck. Scholars were challenged to add and subtract decimals, find area and perimeter using formulas, and stretch their minds even further to calculate volume! Here are some of the incredible trucks scholars produced!

COMING AUGUST 2020!

What You Should Know

The new facility will be located at 10929 Almeda Genoa Rd.
The new facility will be built in two phases.
Phase 1 will be completed for grades 6th-10th, August 2019.
Phase 2 will be completed for grades 1st-12th, August 2020.
Pre-K and Kindergarten will remain at the current location (9701 Almeda Genoa Rd)
We will submit a Pre-K request to the state in February 2019. The state will let us know if we've been
approved for Pre-K sometime before May.

post_text: This past weekend 48 5th graders were privileged to attend the overnight camping trip to Brazos Bend State Park. Scholars learned about light pollution, constellations, and the large telescopes located in the George observatory during their private tour. Some of the highlights of the weekend were cooking hotdogs over the campfire, roasting marshmellows for their s'mores and competing against other teams to find the most wildlife in the Brazos Bend Scavenger hunt. This hands on educational learning experience also created memories that will last a lifetime. Thank you Beta Academy. Thank you Arconic Grant.

Over Spring Break, 10 of our middle school scholars journeyed to Samara, Costa Rica. While there, they were captivated by the country's people and the natural beauty of Costa Rica. They surfed, sea kayaked, snorkeled, zip-lined, gained a new level of independence, and, most importantly, served the local community by painting a community center and sanding old benches. #ichoosebeta #wearebeta
